    "John Trapp": "And when he came to himself ] For till then he had been beside himself, and not his own worthy. Nebulo rascal (saith one) cometh of Nabal; fool of \u03c6\u03b1\u03c5\u03bb\u03bf\u03c2: \u03b1\u03bd\u03bf\u03b9\u03b1 et \u03b1\u03bd\u03bf\u03bc\u03b9\u03b1 are of near affinity. Evil is Hebrew for a fool, &amp;c. Wickedness is called the \"foolishness of madness,\" #Ec 7:25 .\nVer.\n17. And when he came to himself] For till then he had been beside himself, and not his own worthy. Nebulo rascal (saith one) cometh of Nabal; fool of \u03c6\u03b1\u03c5\u03bb\u03bf\u03c2: \u03b1\u03bd\u03bf\u03b9\u03b1 et \u03b1\u03bd\u03bf\u03bc\u03b9\u03b1 are of near affinity. Evil is Hebrew for a fool, &c. Wickedness is called the [v_Ecc_7_25] \"foolishness of madness,\" #Ec 7:"
