    "E.W. Bullinger": "Psa. ii., xlv., cx. Isa. ix. 6, 7).\nF\nverse 16). Twice he refers to it. And why not? What is\nit that makes man hesitate to believe God? These, as we have said, are no mere human beings:\nthey are wicked spirits; and Are not these legion and innumerable?\nThe results of this plague which follow the sounding of the sixth Trumpet are given in\nthe concluding portion of this chapter."
